Expression contains redundant bracket or not
Difficulty: MediumAccuracy: 48.71%Submissions: 35K+Points: 4
Given a string of balanced expression s, check if it contains a redundant parenthesis or not. A set of parenthesis are redundant if the same sub-expression is surrounded by unnecessary or multiple brackets.
Note: Expression may contain + , - , *, and / operators. Given expression is valid and there are no white spaces present.









  class Solution {
  public:
    bool isOperator(char c){
        if(c == '+' or c == '-' or c == '*' or c == '/')return true;
        return false;
    }
    bool checkRedundancy(string &s) {
        stack<char> st;
        for(char &c: s){
            if(c == '(' or isOperator(c)){
                st.push(c);
            }
            else if(c == ')'){
                if(st.empty())return true;
                if(!isOperator(st.top())){
                    return true;
                }
                while(isOperator(st.top()))st.pop();
                if(st.empty())return true;
                if(st.top() != '(')return true;
                st.pop();
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
};
